<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">'''Level 96''' is a racecourse endlessly extending along two perpendicular boundaries. Typical facilities, such as grandstands, stable blocks, stewards’ control rooms, and service structures, run parallel to its two edges without terminating. They serve several purposes other than providing shelter and provisions, as certain rooms are equipped with sports betting services. The ever-present dense fog renders any attempt to traverse the grassy field futile. Beyond the course perimeter lies a surrounding forest of different biomes, though no known fauna species has been identified.</span>
{{Blurimage|file=7399540996 bbef3a9357 k (1).jpg|caption=A guardhouse at nighttime, occupied by mannequins|hovertext=23/01/09}}
<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">Wanderers typically appear 5-10 meters from a corner of the field. The field covers a large portion of the surface area of that level, mostly unobstructed except for a few scattered trees, fencing, and electrical poles. The ground is covered with well-maintained grass without soil exposure. Artificial turf is also visible, sometimes spanning several kilometers wide, used to hide voids. Due to the terrain’s consistency and the fog, spatial disorientation during traversal is common. Naturally, navigational losses have been frequently reported. In addition, food sources are scarce in this region. Remains of several human beings have been found at various locations, whose causes of death are unknown apart from severe trauma in rare cases. Despite the higher humidity and optimal conditions, there are no visible signs of decomposition. In the absence of other alternatives, they are used to derive sustenance. Thus, it is not advisable to explore the field upon arrival, except under emergency scenarios when the location of exit is required.</span>
{{Blurimage|file=5399170367 66a9276c12 k.jpg|caption=A stadium structure seen from the forest area.|hovertext=19/03/16}}
<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">Crossing past the racecourse’s perimeter, the buildings that surround it serve as the secondary area of Level 96. They intersect, implying nonuniform or random generation, and only seldom vary in shape and size. This is because most are buildings serving as impromptu concourses, resembling offices and hallways more than airports, owing to their drop ceiling tiles, minimal illumination, and few furnishings except carpets. In contrast, entirely developed stadium sections can appear, seemingly transported into the environment without consideration. These sections feature amenities imperative for survival (i.e., restaurants, convenience stores, electronic stores, clothing stores, bathrooms with vents). They remain in pristine condition, a strange given, considering their apparent abandonment and proximity to expansive fauna in outer-adjacent zones. Food and beverages also expire later than their expected shelf life. Notwithstanding the presence of aggressive anomalous entities, it remains advisable to stay within their vicinity.</span>
{{Blurimage|file=24250191268 f2225cef13 k.jpg|caption=Typical interior found in large facilities.|hovertext=22/06/95}}
<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">The level’s last environment is a forest, which encompasses the rest of the facilities. This zone is subdivided into a grid system of differing sizes, with boundaries defined by abrupt biome transitions between adjacent grids. One grid may contain a rainforest environment, while its neighbor may consist of tundra, with snowfall confined primarily to that region. Although objects native to Level 96 are restricted to their respective borders, wanderers can travel across them without obstruction. As previously mentioned, the flora found inside the forest is biologically foreign. Even if the flora found within the level bears a physical likeness to real floral species, their internal biological processes are quite dissimilar to those of their surface-level analogs. For example, their coloration is indicative of chlorophyll analogs, yet their respiration patterns use invisible spectra or anomalous radiation, as opposed to sunlight, which is nonexistent inside Level 96. Moreover, the flora can produce fruits, which should not be eaten as no scientific studies have been done to test their safety.</span>
{{Blurimage|file=Pexels-koolshooters-6495060.jpg|caption=Makeshift seating that surrounds the field.|hovertext=30/11/24}}
<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">While a narrow zone of material with a multitude of colors is referenced as part of the forest zone, it is located a few hundred meters from the forest edge. It is made of, when observed through optical instruments, an unlimited number of human corpses. There is no fog in this region. The accumulation of material appears to delineate an invisible border, and information is not available on the condition on the other side of this border.</span>

<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">Level 96’s visibility level is reduced to below 20 meters, sometimes even half that. The ambient air ranges from a consistent 10-15°C, with the indoor environment’s temperature lying in the same range. The day-and-night cycle is 24 hours. Daytime and nighttime both last 12 hours, though there are no sources of light beyond ambient light. There are no further changes except visibility and light level.</span>
<div style="position:relative;width:680px;padding:20px 0;overflow:hidden" class="onlylight"><div style="position:absolute;top:30%;left:0;width:100%;height:70px;background:repeating-linear-gradient(-85deg,rgba(0,64,30,0.3) 2px,rgba(0,64,30,1) 2px,transparent 8px,transparent 18px);opacity:0.6;-webkit-mask-image:linear-gradient(to right,black 60%,transparent 100%);mask-image:linear-gradient(to right,black 60%,transparent 100%);"></div><div style="display:inline-block;z-index:3;position:relative;padding-left:5px;padding-top:25px;font-size:32px;font-family: Holly Groove;"><span style="text-shadow: 0em 0em 1.0em rgba(255,255,255,0.3), 0em 0em 1.0em rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">Entities</span></div></div><div style="position:relative;width:680px;padding:20px 0;overflow:hidden" class="onlydark"><div style="position:absolute;top:30%;left:0;width:100%;height:70px;background:repeating-linear-gradient(-85deg,rgba(0,255,120,0.3) 2px,rgba(0,255,120,1) 2px,transparent 8px,transparent 18px);opacity:0.6;-webkit-mask-image:linear-gradient(to right,black 60%,transparent 100%);mask-image:linear-gradient(to right,black 60%,transparent 100%);"></div><div style="display:inline-block;z-index:3;position:relative;padding-left:5px;padding-top:25px;font-size:32px;font-family: Holly Groove;"><span style="text-shadow: 0em 0em 0.5em black, 0em 0em 0.5em black">Entities</span></div></div>
{{Blurimage|file=2827009388 900c883cfa k.jpg|caption=A restaurant in Level 96, located 200 kilometers away from the starting point. These brightly lit locations can still be hotspots for entity habitation.|hovertext=Day of discovery, 18/07/83}}
<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">Documented entities identified within Level 96 include [[Entity 3|Smilers]], [[Entity 6|Dullers]], [[Entity 8|Hounds]], [[Entity 9|Facelings]], [[Entity 14|Rainbows]], and [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]] (noted as scarce due to high mortality from unknown causes). Curiously, those classified as [https://backrooms.fandom.com/wiki/Category:Anomalous_Entities anomalous], apart from Sportsbetter and Rainbows, are absent, with several discussions among friendly to neutral specimens confirming such. The underlying circumstances remain a mystery, however, as a majority of the interviewees refuse to elaborate beyond attempting to mitigate Level 96 itself. Meanwhile, most entities that inhabit the level tend to be contained inside the facilities, avoiding the outdoors completely. In spite of their sciaphilic nature, they stay inside well-lit areas, even when access to the outdoors during nighttime is unchallenging. Rainbows, on the other hand, are observed only during the daytime. Their emitted light can be viewed weakly at close proximity, but it is not recommended.</span>
{{Blurimage|file=4015866526 d7f7d2f188 k.jpg|caption=A common appearance for halls where the Sportsbetter inhabit.|hovertext=01/02/26}}
=== <span style="font-family: Explore; font-size: 22px;">Sportsbetter</span> ===
<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">Sportsbetter is a 2.7-meter white humanoid entity. It is only encountered in rooms or open spaces explicitly designated as “Betting Halls,” regardless of other factors. As its arms and legs measure approximately twice the length of the torso, its morphology is already visibly disproportionate compared to human anatomy. Additionally, each extremity terminates in four fingers or toes. The integument lacks hair and cuticles and may also be missing distinct epidermal and subdermal layers, as suggested by the absence of sweat and its uniformly homogeneous surface. The surface texture of its “skin” resembles brushed metal, though structural integrity and tensile strength have been documented to be significantly greater since visible injuries, except for its apparent facial features, never appear. Despite this metallic composition, the entity demonstrates fluid and unrestricted movement without surface deformation, abrasion, or mechanical stress marks. As aforementioned, facial anatomy is restricted to holes and cuts that Sportsbetter itself calls its “eyes” and “mouth.” Two cylindrical perforations function as ocular structures, which the entity self-identifies as the “eyes.” Meanwhile, oral features are variably present, sometimes manifesting as a jagged, burr-lined gash extending deeply into the region corresponding to the jaw. The entity emits a low-intensity luminescence. In complete darkness, Sportsbetter’s entire body becomes sharply visible and appears brightly illuminated with subtle, ambient light outlining its silhouette, exhibiting contrast inconsistent with other white objects beside it.</span>

<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">When these wanderers spend a few minutes in a predetermined betting hall, Sportsbetter is known to manifest and make contact with them. Manifestation is said to take place without any noticeable precursor, whereby Sportsbetter may appear sitting with its back turned away from the subject, or even while practicing speeches in a stage area, provided there is one. Although literacy is questionable, the entity is fluent in several languages, such as English, Mandarin Chinese, Spanish, French, Malay (including Indonesian/Malay continuum), Japanese, Korean, Cantonese, Tamil, Irish, Welsh, and Scottish Gaelic. Certain individuals who do not speak any of the mentioned languages are noted to communicate through non-verbal ways, such as approximate hand gestures, with Sportsbetter. The consequences for those who do not wish to interact with Sportsbetter, as well as for persons who enter a betting Hall but then leave before the entity manifests, remain undocumented.</span>

<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">Interaction usually begins when the wanderer is shocked by Sportsbetter’s sudden appearance. If the wanderer does not immediately flee, the entity responds mimetically as if it is also surprised and questions the wanderer’s identity and presence. Due to its uncanny appearance, the initial exchange of the conversation circles superficial details about the victim and the entity, where Sportsbetter offers a stated reason for its bodily appearance. Sportsbetter also bears a name tag with a randomized numerical identifier, leading to a longer discussion and a bridge toward more personal information. The entity is known for its high emotional intelligence and can manipulate wanderers over time, which concludes with the victim being convinced to bet on likely fictitious horse races, but they are nonetheless perceived to be taking place in the level shown through projections or screens. In every observed instance, Sportsbetter wins.</span>

<span  style="font-family: Plus Jakarta Sans;">Up to this point, the fate of the wanderer remains undetermined. Reports indicate that the numerical identifier on Sportsbetter’s name tag re-scrambles following its gambling victory, while other accounts describe the entity placing a blank firearm or blunt-edged knife on a table. In all recorded instances involving survivors, the moments between discovering the betting hall and the final conversation with Sportsbetter are described as being solely a dream.</span>
