<div style="z-index: 999; opacity: 0; animation: grow-unfade 4s forwards; animation-delay: 8s; position: relative; width: 100%; bottom: 1000px; transform-origin: top center;"><center><div style="background-color: white; margin: 1em; padding: 67px; text-align: justify; font-family: JMH Typewriter Sans; font-size: 18px; border: solid 3px black; color: black; transform: skew(-0.2deg);">
AUDIO RECORDING TRANSCRIPT<br>
Recording ID: INT-CLR-041<br>
Date: 2019-06-14<br>
Location: Unspecified Interior<br>
Participants:<br>
* Ernesto “Ernie” St. Clair, First Speaker
* Domingo Ibáñez, Second Speaker

[00:28:07] St. Clair: You meet that girl?

[00:28:10] Ibáñez: We in the talking stage, yeah. Is my first time in a while, so… take it easy on me, amigo.

[00:28:16] St. Clair: A woman a woman, man. You gotta respect that. Worst she can say is no.

[00:28:22] Ibáñez: Don’t start with me.

[00:28:24] St. Clair: I’m just playin’, relax.

[00:28:27] Ibáñez: Anyway, man. She used to be a lawyer. So the difficulty, it go up a little bit, no?

[00:28:32] St. Clair: Yo, that ain’t harder than the bar exam.

[00:28:36] Ibáñez: What’s that? The bar exam?

[00:28:38] St. Clair: You ain’t never seen Law & Order? Better Call Saul?

[00:28:42] Ibáñez: I don’t watch shows like that.

[00:28:45] St. Clair: Dude, they don’t just hand that job out. Bar exam a big test. You pass it, you a lawyer.

[00:28:53] Ibáñez: And if you don’t pass?

[00:28:55] St. Clair: Then you don’t become one. Simple. Kinda like how you sittin’ right now.

[00:29:01] Ibáñez: Me? What I do?

[00:29:05] St. Clair: …Nothing.

[00:29:06 – 00:29:41]<br>
Footsteps on concrete. Mild echo. No speech.

[00:29:42] SYSTEM NOTE: Approx. 6 minutes of audio missing.

[00:35:18] Ibáñez: —so I get this cookbook from his office, right? I’m thinkin’ maybe I cook somethin’, impress her a little. He ain’t even have his gun there that day.

[00:35:28] St. Clair: Mm.

[00:35:30] Ibáñez: It played out just like this. Hands in my pockets. Walkin. Lookin’ around. I felt safe. Too safe, maybe. I tiptoe to the desk, open one shelf and—man—the wood loud as hell. Like droppin’ a bottle at three in the mornin’ when everybody asleep.

[00:35:48] St. Clair: Dom.

[00:35:49] Ibáñez: Hm?

[00:35:51] St. Clair: You saw?

[00:35:53] Ibáñez: Saw what?

[00:35:55] St. Clair: The sign.

[00:35:57] Ibáñez: What sign?

[00:35:59] St. Clair: You said you was lookin’ around.

[00:36:02] Ibáñez: Yeah. Back in the office. Not here, Ernstein.

[00:36:05] St. Clair: Nah. Here. Right now. Focus.

[00:36:09] Ibáñez: Why you sound like that?

[00:36:12] St. Clair: There’s chairs in here, dude.

[00:36:15] Ibáñez: …Okay?

[00:36:17] St. Clair: Chairs and tables. Set up.

[00:36:20] Ibáñez: You never been on Earth—

[00:36:23]<br>
Footsteps change direction.

[00:36:25] Ibáñez: Hey. Where you goin’?

[00:36:27] St. Clair: I’m gettin’ the hell out.

[00:36:30] Ibáñez: You gonna die if you do that.

[00:36:33] St. Clair: What?

[00:36:35] Ibáñez: What, you never been to the Back—

[00:36:37] St. Clair: Don’t start that cryptic mess right now.

[00:36:41] Ibáñez: Look, I got an idea.

[00:36:43] St. Clair: This ain’t the time for ideas, yo—

[00:36:46 – 00:36:52]<br>
Metallic clink. Object picked up.

[00:36:53] Ibáñez: If it land heads, we record the guy. If it heads again, it you who talk.

[00:37:00] St. Clair: Dom, we can’t just stand here flippin’ coins.

[00:37:04]<br>
Coin flip.

[00:37:06] Ibáñez: …Heads.

[00:37:08]<br>
Coin flip.

[00:37:10] Ibáñez: Tails.

[00:37:12] St. Clair: Dom.

[00:37:14] Ibáñez: Okay, okay. Wait. I take out my phone. I go there. Just give me second.

[00:37:20]<br>
Distant creaking intensifies. Low electrical hum begins under the recording. Voices become partially muffled, as if obstructed by fabric or interference.

[00:37:24] Ibáñez (muffled): You hear that?

[00:37:26] St. Clair (muffled): Yeah. Don’t like that.

[00:37:29]<br>
Footsteps slow. Chair leg scraping faintly across floor.

[00:37:32] Ibáñez (muffled, louder): Sportsbetter?

[00:37:35] St. Clair (muffled, sharp whisper): No. We don’t call him that.

[00:37:39] Ibáñez (muffled): Uh… hello?

[00:37:42] St. Clair (muffled): Sir?

[00:37:45] Unknown Voice: Oh, hey.

[00:37:48]<br>
Brief static distortion.

[00:37:50] Ibáñez (muffled): What’re you working on?

[00:37:53] Unknown Voice: Me?

[00:37:55] St. Clair (muffled): Yeah.

[00:37:58] Unknown Voice: Some… detective novel.

[00:38:03] Ibáñez (muffled): Oh. Cool. How you write with those… hands?

[00:38:08]<br>
Pause. Light tapping sound. Possibly fingernails on wood.

[00:38:11] Unknown Voice: You wanna critique it for me?

[00:38:15] St. Clair (muffled): I mean… if we got time.

[00:38:19] Unknown Voice: It’s about this KGB officer. Bit like Gordievsky. He betrays his superiors, then—y’know—yadda yadda. I know a lotta stuff. I just don’t like being insensitive.

[00:38:32] Ibáñez (muffled): Insensitive?

[00:38:35] Unknown Voice: Yeah, man. Better to fictionalize things.

[00:38:41] St. Clair (muffled): You know… that kinda sound like you, Dom.

[00:38:46] Ibáñez (muffled): Come on, man…

[00:38:49] Unknown Voice: That sounds… fun.

[00:38:53] St. Clair (muffled): Can’t you at least critique his novel?

[00:38:58] Ibáñez (muffled): Sure. I mean… we kill time with it, right?

[00:39:04]<br>
Chair creaks. Paper shifting.

[00:39:07] Unknown Voice: I’m just a bit… nervous.

[00:39:11]<br>
Low hum deepens slightly.

[00:39:13] Unknown Voice: I hope you don’t forget where you’re at. Or put too much focus on me.

[00:39:20]<br>
Silence.

[00:39:22] Unknown Voice (quieter): Like Ibáñez does.

[00:39:27]<br>
Recording distortion increases.

[00:39:31] St. Clair (muffled): —nah, we straight—

[00:39:34] Ibáñez (muffled): —just read the first—

[00:39:37] Unknown Voice (partially intelligible): …you’ll see what I mean…

[00:39:41]<br>
Abrupt spike of static.

[00:39:44 – 01:08:12]<br>
SYSTEM NOTE: Approx. 28 minutes of audio missing. File resumes mid-conversation. Ambient hum lower than before. Voices heavily muffled.

[01:08:13] Unknown Voice: —and as you know, I’m very much alike.

[01:08:18]<br>
Paper shifting.

[01:08:20] Unknown Voice: Have you got any snacks? I got the win, so I deserve an award. That right?

[01:08:27] Ibáñez (muffled): Um. Sure. Hershey’s.

[01:08:32] Unknown Voice: They taste like vomit, don’t they?

[01:08:36] Ibáñez: Yeah. I think so.

[01:08:39] Unknown Voice: That’s the best you got? For Valentine’s?

[01:08:43] Ibáñez: I mean… didn’t have time.

[01:08:47] Unknown Voice: Sure you do.

[01:08:50] Ibáñez: What?

[01:08:52] St. Clair (muffled): Hold on, man—

[01:08:55]<br>
Sharp shushing sound.

[01:08:57] Unknown Voice: Shh. Escúchame, Domingo.

[01:09:07]<br>
Unintelligible response.

[01:09:10] Unknown Voice: La vas a tratar bien, ¿verdad?

[01:09:14] Ibáñez (unsteady): Yo… yo voy.

[01:09:18]<br>
SYSTEM NOTE: Previous live auto-caption feed failure. All subsequent captioning has been corrected automatically.

[01:09:21] Unknown Voice: Let me have the chocolate, won’t you?

[01:09:24] Ibáñez: Sure. Sure. Go ahead.

[01:09:28] Wrapper crinkling. Distinct wet smacking sound. Irregular  chewing. Wrapper falls to floor.

[01:09:36] Unknown Voice: Where’d you get this anyway? From Spain? Spanish?

[01:09:42] Ibáñez: No. America.

[01:09:45] Unknown Voice: America. Land of the Free.

[01:09:51]<br>
Chair leg drags.

[01:09:54] Ibáñez: Look, man. Can he… can he go?

[01:09:59] Unknown Voice: Where’d you make friends with St. Claire?

[01:10:04] Ibáñez: Saint… Claire?

[01:10:07] Unknown Voice: You know anyone back in America, Mr. Ibáñez? Are they just like you? Do they eat shitty chocolate, too?

[01:10:16] Ibáñez: Sportsbetter, please. I can’t seem to understand—

[01:10:20] Unknown Voice: Take your time. There’s someone you remember.

[01:10:28] Ibáñez: I don’t think so.

[01:10:31] Unknown Voice: Hm? You don’t think so? Well, it’s either yes or no.

[01:10:36] Ibáñez: I don’t know much about chocolates, okay?

[01:10:41] Unknown Voice: I mean… you walked and ran and starved all the way here. Right? I got you here, too. You and I put a lot of effort into dragging you here. So we all get to hear the story as many times as we want.

[01:10:57]<br>
Silence. Low hum rises slightly.

[01:11:12] Unknown Voice: All right. We go that way. How about another critique, Dom? You’ve still got one chapter left.

[01:11:20] Ibáñez: No, man. You don’t get it…

[01:11:21]<br>
Extended silence. Subtle gulping sound. Breathing uneven.

[01:12:05] Unknown Voice: Oh, goodness. Those crocodile tears. What did Earth ever do to you?

[01:12:13] Ibáñez: Nothing…

[01:12:17] Unknown Voice: I agree. Nothing. Do you agree, Ibáñez?

[01:12:23] Ibáñez: I agree.

[01:12:26] Unknown Voice: Say it again.

[01:12:29] Ibáñez: I agree.

[01:12:33] Unknown Voice: How about you? You do anything to Lara?

[01:12:38] St. Clair: No, man.

[01:12:42] Unknown Voice: I don’t agree. You did something. Is that it, Ibáñez?

[01:12:49] Ibáñez: That’s all there is, man. Please.

[01:12:55] Unknown Voice: Repeat after me, Mr. Ibáñez. That’s all there is.

[01:13:02]<br>
Silence.

[01:13:07] Unknown Voice: Mr. Ibáñez?

[01:13:11] Ibáñez (clear): That’s all there is.

[01:13:18] Unknown Voice: Now, you’ll remember.

[01:13:20]<br>
Long pause. Hum diminishes abruptly.

[01:14:02] Unknown Voice (normal tone): Goodbye, Ibáñez and St. Claire. Nice meeting you both.

[01:14:10]<br>
No immediate response.

[01:14:15] Unknown Voice: You’ve got something to say?

[01:14:22]<br>
Footsteps. Two sets. Slow at first, then quicker. Doorframe creak. Ambient hum ceases completely.

[02:03:11]<br>
Paper movement. Multiple pages turning slowly.

[02:03:14] Unknown Voice (muffled): Judge. Jury. Executioner.

[02:03:20]<br>
Pages continue rustling.

[02:03:22] Unknown Voice (muffled): Judge. Jury. Executioner.

[02:03:28]<br>
Pause.

[02:03:31] Unknown Voice (muffled): That’s what the Rome Statute of the International Criminal Court says? Article 25?

[02:03:39]<br>
Distant structural rumbling. Possibly external corridor. Chair legs scrape faintly.

[02:03:45]<br>
Footsteps growing fainter. Doorframe vibration. Low-frequency distortion.

[02:03:52]<br>
AUDIO INTERRUPTION.

[DATA CORRUPTED]

[02:04:07]<br>
Audio fully drops.

[02:04:—]<br>
SYSTEM ALERT: Recording unexpectedly resumes without user input.

[02:04:33]
Continuous rustling. Multiple books displaced rapidly. Heavy object impacts wooden surface. Tables dragged across floor.

[02:05:14]<br>
SYSTEM NOTE: Environmental audio suggests interior rearrangement of objects without visible mechanical cause.

[02:05:26]<br>
Impact sound. Microphone shifts position.

[02:05:37] END OF RECOVERABLE MATERIAL
