=== <span style="font-family: Explore; font-size: 22px;">Entrances</span> ===
* In [[Level 2]], entering a door labeled “Betting Hall” leads one to Level 96’s racecourse.
* Quantum fluctuations in [[Level 3.14]] oddly carry wanderers here.
* Noclipping through a seafloor covered with artificial turf in [[Level 7]].
* When it rains in [[Level 72]], there is a chance that the mist afterward may gradually obscure one’s surroundings, transporting one here.
* Crossing a bridge to an island shrouded with dense fog in [[Level 974]] will cause the environment to subtly transition to this level.

=== <span style="font-family: Explore; font-size: 22px;">Exits</span> ===
* Staring at the line of bodies at the end of the forest may cause one to be distracted, before falling through leaf litter to [[Level 13]].
* A patch of snow in the racecourse area delivers one to [[Level 35]].
* Crossing into an oddly orange-tinted grid of forest (including the air) takes wanderers to [[Level 85]].
* While rare and dangerous to perform due to the number of entities, cupboards present in this level’s few restaurants may contain a sliding wall behind them. This grants access to a narrow passageway that directly sends one to [[Level 123]].
* Contrastingly, leaping into an anomalously glitching patch of grass can lead one to [[Level 199]], but this occurrence is uncommon.
* An under-construction section within Level 96’s facilities may strangely have asphalt as its floor, which, when noclipped through, transfers one to [[Level 690]].
* Digging deep into the ground covered in imitation ground may cause one to plunge into the [[The Void]], where wanderers spend an indeterminate amount of time in that space before landing in a random level.</div></div>
